data.title: Yummy fish and chips
data.text: We went here for lunch after my son's basketball game. The fish and chips were excellent. I loved the fried oysters and the kids loved the chicken tenders. I felt like everything was fresh and made to order. I will go back again.

data.title: Great food and staff
data.text: This is a small fish and chips place, but it is a cut above. You go up to the counter to order, and the food comes to your table. Typical disposable utensils and plates, but the difference here is the staff and food. The staff is extremely helpful and friendly. Whoever trained these young men did an amazing job - not your typical fast food place AT ALL. And the food was unexpectedly good. Example - you can order your fish and chips to include some calamari or fried oysters. Everything we tried was great.

data.title: Fourth & Sea
data.text: Went to this restaurant for dinner and wow was it delicious. We had fish and chips and great fresh steak fries. The staff were really attentive and owner is really nice.

data.title: Milkshakes
data.text: This place has some amazing milkshakes. Mine was super creamy and rich. They also have a nice car show during the summer months. I highly recommend it.

data.title: Wonderful fish and chips!
data.text: Friendly owner, fresh food, fast service-a real gem of an eatery. Food was hot, garlic fries were delicious and I wish I could have tried their burgers and chili spaghetti!!!  The calamari was okay, not my favorite but I like marinara with my calamari so that may have been the issue-they only had cocktail sauce. The guy next to us had a shrimp Louie salad which looked amazing and all their dressings are homemade. Bonus!

data.title: Yummy
data.text:
This, street corner (4th & C St) restaurant didn't disappoint...it was great.  Had their fish and chips...excellent.
The staff was fun, looked like they were having fun, and made us feel very comfortable.  The restaurant was constantly busy.

data.title: Dog friendly with water bowl!
data.text: We stopped for lunch because we had a puppy and the rebiews said dog friendly. Yes, we were given a water bowl for our puppy. Plenty of patio seating. The food delicious. Great fish and chips! Save room for an ice cream cone. Yummy!

data.title: Come for the Fish & Chips with Coleslaw!!
data.text: My husband and I visited Petaluma for the day. We came to Fourth and Sea for dinner. We ate fish and chips with coleslaw for dinner. The food was good, so was the value of the food and nice service.

data.title: Good food, Great Portions!
data.text: Went with a group. The corner restaurant is the perfect spot to sit outside on a cool day and watch passer-bys while enjoying great food. The service is VERY attentive, and the menu items are fantastic. The restaurant is near all the downtown shops,was easy to find, and has ample parking. Garlic fries and fish tacos were huge and delicious! The beef hot dogs were plump and tasty! They do permit dogs in the outdoor seating area if you're taking your canine with you.

data.title: Simply consistently good
data.text:
This place is great. I've been a few times over the past months l, trying different items each time. Each time it's good.
I know no matter what I order at this point it will be prepared quickly and consistently. I have found a few places I really like since moving here. Well prepared affordable seafood and burgers I as hard to beat as it gets.

data.title: Consistently good!
data.text: My husband and I get dinner from Fourth and Sea every few months and it has never been anything but great.  We split the #10, which is plenty of food for two people with moderate appetites.  It has fish, fries, coleslaw, and your choice of prawns, oysters or chicken and is a good price for dinner for two people.  The chocolate dipped ice cream cone is also the best soft serve in town.  The service here is quick and friendly and if you don't feel like getting out of your car, they have a to-go parking spot where you can call in your order, and they bring out your food and take your payment in the parking lot.  There is a small parking lot out back if you want to dine in, but street parking usually isn't too difficult.

data.title: Fish, Oysters, Milk Shakes, Oh My!
data.text: Save a trip to North Florida--have their Fish and Chips/cole slaw!  Crispy large portions of fish, nicely seasoned large cut fries and a creamy, yet light cole slaw--perfect lunch after a long morning bike ride!  We also split an order of fried oysters, which were very large and rich in flavor, but not overly salty.  The milk shake was just like I'd make at home, not some artificial mixture sitting around in a dispenser all day. The service was great, although the owner was training a newbie on the first day we were there.  The kid was definitely a quick learner, knew something about customer service and looking for things to do when things were slow.  Probably still in High School, we were impressed with his cool, "yes sir" attitude towards the much more aggressive (but sensitive) owner.  Great place, great people and we will be back next trip.  Stopped there twice this time.  Hamburgers on toasted Hoagi roll looked good (although we didn't have one).

data.title: Another GREAT meal
data.text: My wife & I stopped to have dinner before the movie, she had fish tacos that were great an I had the chili spaghetti which was also great, never a disappointing meal anything they serve has always been good, everyone is friendly and helpful

data.title: Locals know this gem!
data.text: This place has something for everyone. Seafood, burgers, salads and ice cream! I had the burger and a side of chili. My spouse had the #10 . It was a ton of food. I'm not a fan of disposable flatware and plates, but I put up with the picnic presentation because the food was freshly prepared and the service was friendly. Make a point to stop by if you're in Petaluma !

data.title: Best fish and chips in town!
data.text: Yum!!  Huge portions and the fish and chips are hot and fresh. Highly recommend!  My children all love the fish and chips served here.

data.title: Wonderful
data.text:
Don't miss this gem . I had fish tacos, they were delicious.My husband had fish and chips..he thought they were the best he ever had.   
Please think of franchise.....

data.title: Outstanding seafood that won't break the bank!
data.text: This place won't get awards for their building, but they should for their food! Located on a corner near the old city center, it has seating both indoors and outdoors. You and order at an outside window or at the counter inside. The food will be brought out to you. I had the single fish and chips plate and my fish was gigantic. My wife had a fried oyster (she's on a diet) and the shrimp louie salad. Everything was yummy. And, as I said, I didn't have to mortgage the house to pay the bill.

data.title: Affordable and Delicious Artery Cloggery
data.text:
Oh mama. Whenever I drive past this place, I regret not stopping. It's cheap and really good food. The fish always tastes fresh, 

If you are visiting Petaluma, stop in while you are walking downtown. it isn't far from the Museum downtown, only a block.

data.title: Excellent Fish and Chips
data.text:
We ordered the one-piece fish and chips with cole slaw, price was $7.95.  The order came really fast.  The fish was excellent quality, done to perfection.  Tasty cole slaw, thick french fries.
Wait staff walked around with white shirts and bow ties.  They were attentive and solicitous.  Restaurant saved money bypserving everything on styrofoam with plastic utensils.  Who care, the food was great!

data.title: Great seafood, very low prices, sweet service
data.text: I know, I'm devaluing "five starts" by giving this rating to a hole in the wall.  But this place really is good.  I usually get the shrimp louie.  The half order is what they recommend because its really pretty large.  For about $7.00 its also a great deal.  The shrimp is plentiful and comes with boiled egg, beans, beets, the whole shabang.  This place also has a direct line into what ever factory turns out perfect serving staff.  These are mainly young people who are uniformly friendly, caring, polite, light-hearted, and just plain charming.  They even have trivial pursuit cards on the tables to keep one occupied while the food is cooked.  My wife and I had dinner there the other night for under $20.  Ok, so there's no wine or beer.  The decor is "understated" (i.e. its an old Foster's Freeze, converted into a site down place, so don't expect much).  But for me, its five stars.  Great food, service and value makes up for any lack of glamour.
